N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. tit. 1, ch. I, subch. B, pt. 20

Statutory authority: Agriculture and Markets Law, §§16, 18, 258-k, 258-m, 258-n, 294

The provisions of Order No. 2 of the Secretary of

Agriculture of the United States are identical with those of official Order No. 126, as promulgated by the Commissioner of Agriculture and Markets of the State
of New York, herein designated as Part 20. Such orders are joint and concurrent
and are jointly administered. For the purpose of continuing such uniformity, sections appear in the Official Compilation under Federal Order
designations. State regulations are updated quarterly; we currently have two versions available. Below is a
comparison between our most recent version and the prior quarterly release. More comparison features will be added as we have more versions to compare. No prior version found.
